<item>
            <title>[LU-6135] improved support for selecting specific OSTs for files</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6135</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4665&quot; title=&quot;utils: lfs setstripe to specify OSTs&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4665&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4665&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &quot;utils: lfs setripe to specify OSTs&quot; support was added to &lt;tt&gt;lfs setstripe&lt;/tt&gt; to allow specifying a list or range of OSTs on which to create a new file using the &lt;tt&gt;-o&lt;/tt&gt; option.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be useful to fully support this functionality using other methods such as setting default directory layouts and using the new &lt;tt&gt;llapi_layout_*&lt;/tt&gt; API.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
